<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<pretext xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:ns1="https://prefigure.org">
    <ns0:include href="../docinfo.ptx" />
    <article>
        <section xml:id="ps08-section">
            <title>Problem Set 8</title>

            <subtitle>Sequences and Series</subtitle>
            <ns0:include href="ps03.ptx" xpointer="xpointer(//section[1]/introduction)" />
            <exercises>
                <exercise xml:id="ex-sequence-convergence-revised">
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p> Determine whether the <alert>sequence</alert> <m>a_n =
                                \frac{3n^2+1}{n^2-2}</m> converges or diverges. If it converges,
                                find its limit. </p>
                        </statement>

                        </task>
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p> Determine whether the <alert>series</alert> <m>\sum_{n=0}^\infty
                                \frac{3n^2+1}{n^2-2}</m> converges or diverges. If it converges,
                                find its limit. </p>
                        </statement>
                        </task>
                </exercise>

                <exercise xml:id="ex-Rogawksi-11-02-13">
                    <introduction>
                        <p> Consider the series <m>\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{4n^2-1}</m>. </p>
                    </introduction>
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                                Evaluate the first five partial sums of the series.
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                        </task>
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                                Evaluate the sum of the series.
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                        </task>
                </exercise>

                <exercise xml:id="ex-Rogawski-11-03-45">
                    <statement>
                        <figure>
                            <image>
                                <ns1:prefigure label="prefig-ex-Rogawski-11-03-45">
                                    <ns1:diagram dimensions="(300,300)" margins="5">
                                        <ns1:definition>NyuViolet="#57068c"</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:definition>UltraViolet="#8900e1"</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:definition>MediumViolet1="#702b9d"</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:definition>MediumViolet2="#7b5aa6"</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:definition>LightViolet1="#ab82c5"</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:definition>LightViolet2="#eee6f3"</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:definition>a=0.5</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:definition>b=0</ns1:definition>
                                        <ns1:coordinates bbox="(-0.2,-0.2,1.2,1.2)">
                                            <ns1:polygon points="((0,0),(1,0),(1,1))" closed="yes" stroke="NyuViolet" />
                                            <ns1:repeat parameter="k=1..8">
                                                <ns1:polygon points="((b,b),(1,b),(a,a))" closed="no" stroke="UltraViolet" />
                                                <ns1:definition>b=a</ns1:definition>
                                                <ns1:definition>a=(1+a)/2</ns1:definition>
                                            </ns1:repeat>
                                            <ns1:label anchor="(0.5,0)" alignment="s" color="#8900e1">
                                                <ns1:m>1</ns1:m>
                                            </ns1:label>
                                            <ns1:angle-marker points="((1,0),(0,0),(1,1))" thickness="1">
                                                <ns1:m>\pi/4</ns1:m>
                                            </ns1:angle-marker>
                                            <ns1:angle-marker points="((0.5,0.5),(1,0),(0,0))" thickness="1">
                                                <ns1:m>\pi/4</ns1:m>
                                            </ns1:angle-marker>
                                        </ns1:coordinates>
                                    </ns1:diagram>
                                </ns1:prefigure>
                            </image>
                        </figure>
                        <p> Use a geometric series to find the total length of the infinite zigzag
                            path shown in the figure (each zag occurs at an angle of <m>
                            \frac{\pi}{4}</m>). </p>
                    </statement>
                    </exercise>

                <exercise xml:id="ex-integral-test">
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p> Use the integral test to determine if the series <m>\sum_{n=2}^\infty
                                \frac{1}{n^3-n^2+n-1}</m> converges. Evaluate the improper integral. </p>
                        </statement>
                        </task>
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p> Use the limit comparison test to determine if the series <m>\sum_{n=2}^\infty
                                \frac{1}{n^3-n^2+n-1}</m> converges. </p>
                        </statement>
                        </task>
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                                Compare and contrast the two methods.
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                        </task>
                </exercise>

                <exercise xml:id="ex-comparison-test">
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p> Use the comparison test to determine whether the series <m>\sum_{n=1}^\infty
                                \frac{\cos^2 n}{n^2+1}</m> converges or diverges. </p>
                        </statement>

                        </task>
                    <task>
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                                Can the limit comparison test be used instead? Why or why not?
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                        </task>
                </exercise>
            </exercises>
        </section>
    </article>
</pretext>